         <abstract>
            <p>There has been too ready acceptance of the idea that a number of expert or administrative devices can solve problems of conflict and coordination. Greatest difficulties arise from confusion and conflict in exercise of government functions. In recent years, the Federal Government granted new aids to the states, and then invaded state revenue sources to finance them. Progress depends on controlling underlying policies which increase conflicts. The states should eliminate needless differences in forms, filing and tax due dates, definitions, etc., which create unnecessary compliance costs.</p>
